{
  "stem": "18770.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were always observant.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That had never stopped.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, the very fact that we found a kosher restaurant [LAUGHS] in Tokyo speaks to the desire to be observant.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My parents joined a synagogue near where we live.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I still remember its name, the West Side Institutional Synagogue, about a few blocks from where we live.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We go every Saturday morning for the services.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We are enrolled in their Sunday School-- my sister and I, you know, and cousins.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father has a job.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father's life is pretty unhappy once we come to the States.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had married-- by marrying my mother, he had married into a wealthy family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Poland, he had become-- by marrying my mother, he had been named one of the directors of this very large, prosperous family.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we lived that way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By the time we come to New York, my grandfather-- who was the nominal, at least, head of, you know, titular head of the family-- he dies of cancer shortly after we come to the, you know, the United States, say, within six or eight months of the time we come there.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my father's future, you might say, is at the discretion financially of his brothers-in-law, who are not that favorably disposed to him.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And while they become-- my, my two uncles who have traveled out with us join the uncle who had come through Cuba and the one with the money in becoming directors of this new chocolate family-- factory which they started in New York.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father becomes the expediter there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, he runs basically-- a sort of a glorified shipping clerk.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember that as a child.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
